FBIS4-39985 "drsov113_b_94033" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 12 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military, Nuclear & Space Issues Smolensk Nuclear Plant Reportedly Undamaged After Flood Smolensk Nuclear Plant Reportedly Undamaged After Flood LD1206122794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1100 GMT 12 Jun 94 LD1206122794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Our special correspondent Dmitriy Motrich reported over the phone from Smolensk today that a natural disaster had occurred last night in Smolensk Oblast, not far from the town of Roslavl, the site of the Smolensk nuclear power station. Torrential rains broke a dam, houses were flooded, and farms destroyed. The area has lost its electricity and communications lines. The number of victims is still unclear. According to preliminary reports, the nuclear power station itself is unharmed. Our correspondents have already arrived at the site, and we will keep you posted.
